I actively assisted students in Mathematics, Biology, and Economics, addressing both olympiad preparation and the regular curriculum.  My teaching philosophy is flexible, adapting to the unique needs of each student. I strive to present information in a concise and easily digestible manner. Rather than relying on traditional lecture-style teaching, I engage students by guiding them through collaborative exercises and questions. This approach allows us to work through challenges together, fostering a deeper understanding of the material.  I prioritize a hands-on approach, emphasizing the completion of numerous exercises. By creating a supportive environment, I encourage students to explore solutions independently while providing guidance to develop their critical thinking skills. This method not only facilitates learning but also empowers students to navigate challenges with a well-developed thought process. Overall, my goal is to instill confidence and promote a genuine understanding of the subject matter in each student I work with.
